        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 11 at 7:32PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Higgins, or 13 miles southwest of Shattuck. This thunderstorm was
nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Higgins.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
